SIMPLE: indispensable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indispensable
<hw>In`dis*pen"sa*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>dispensable</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>indispensable</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not dispensable; impossible to be omitted, remitted,
or spared; absolutely necessary or requisite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>Not admitting dispensation; not
subject to release or exemption.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The law was moral and <qex>indispensable</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Burnet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Unavoidable; inevitable.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indispensableness</ent>⟦br⟧
